overview: The user initiated a request to evaluate an existing codebase for a
  "Sleep Questionnaire Application" against a provided Statement of Work (SOW).
  The primary goal was to implement a database for questionnaire responses, a
  client-facing dashboard, and any necessary middleware for authentication. The
  user expressed a preference for NeonDB and the simplest possible solution. The
  agent developed a plan that included updating demographics, creating a Prisma
  schema for , implementing API routes for data storage
  and CSV export, and building a simple admin dashboard with a login page.
  Initially, a custom session management system was proposed, but it was later
  simplified to leverage Next.js middleware for authentication, providing a
  cleaner and more efficient solution. The agent guided the user through
  database setup and environment variable configuration, then successfully
  tested the questionnaire submission, admin login, and data retrieval
  functionalities via the browser.
